Wimbledon Champion Djokovic Pulls Out of Davis Cup Match With Knee Injury

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-07-08T13:29:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/wimbledon-champion-djokovic-pulls-out-of-davis-cup-match-with-knee-injury.html
Australian Open and Wimbledon
champion Novak Djokovic pulled out of  Serbia ’s opening Davis Cup
match with Sweden’s Ervin Eleskovic with an injury to his left
knee, the competition’s organizers said today.  The top-ranked man on the ATP tour decided he wouldn’t play
about 40 minutes before the start of the match and was replaced
by  Janko Tipsarevic , according to a statement on the Davis Cup
website. Sweden is hosting defending champions Serbia in a
quarterfinal of the event.  The Davis Cup is the largest annual international men’s
tennis tournament.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  